Diagnosis.
Male arista without or with 1–3 short ventral branch(es) distally, the longest ventral branch as long as 1/3 the longest dorsal branch (
Fig. 7A
); posterior bands of male abdominal third to fifth tergites connect to lateral margins (
Fig. 5B
); male abdominal sixth tergite narrow laterally (
Fig. 7B
).
